name: 350 acres with 1km creek, 4x4, bike
description: Beautiful peaceful forest away from the city with easy 4X4 access and a nice river.  Kangaroos and goats. Wild berries. Existing campsite, extraordinary serenity. Many interesting bike trails, creek is mainly permanent, it has been known to be dry, not since I started using Peter Andrews and Victor Schaubergers techniques.The spacebeautiful pine forrest, respectful open camp fires allowed in times of low-risk fire dangerOther things to noteObey all signageLicense numberExempt
additional_house_rules: With the highest respect for Mother Earth and all for whom she provides.

description: "The Shed" is located in the heart of the historic gold mining village of Tuena with views over Tuena Creek.The shed has been recently renovated as a cosy and comfy two bedroom cabin  that can sleep up to 4 guests. It is complete with a full kitchen (oven, microwave, fridge - freezer), outside ensuite, air conditioning/heating and  TV/DVD, wifi.It is conveniently located behind "Parsons General Store" which offers supplies & alcohol.  The village of Tuena is located 56km north of Crookwell.The spaceTuena is a small, friendly village and ideal for a relaxing get away and is situated halfway between Goulburn and Orange. Abercrombie Caves and river are a short distance away.Other things to noteThere is only the general store nearby that sells alcohol and basic groceries. transit: As the Shed is in a small rural village there is no public transport.
